hildren":"•"}],["$","span",null,{"children":"5 min read"}]]}]]}],["$","article",null,{"className":"ArticleLayout_content___Im_T","children":[["$","p",null,{"children":"The fact that traditional business plans were designed for a pre-COVID world—one characterized by more centralized and predictable workforce structures, predictable supply chains, and linear growth assumptions is a clarion call for a new approach. In the Post-COVID, AI Era™, these assumptions no longer hold and have been replaced by markets that now shift faster, work that is decentralized, customer behavior that is less predictable, and AI technological acceleration, which has introduced non-linear change. Static, document-centric plans struggle to remain relevant under these conditions."}],"$L6","$L7","$L8","$L9","$La","$Lb","$Lc","$Ld","$Le","$Lf","$L10","$L11","$L12"]}]]}],"$L13"],["$L14","$L15"],"$L16"]}],{},null,false]},null,false]},null,false]},null,false],"$L17",false]],"m":"$undefined","G":["$18",[]],"s":false,"S":true}
